Ping Pong with Node.js, Express, Socket.IO
---------------------------------------------------------------

Operations :
Server:
-Sends a PONG response when it receives a PING message from the client;
-Outputs the message to the console when it gets a PONG response from the server
-Emits a PING message to a client at random intervals of 5 to 10 second.

Client:
-Sends a PONG response when it receives a PING message from the server
-Outputs the message to the Web console when it gets a PONG response from the server
-Emits a PING message to the server when a user clicks a Submit button


---------------------------------------------------------------
Required Softwares:

-Node v0.13.0-pre
	Dependencies:
	"body-parser": "~1.10.2",
    "cookie-parser": "~1.3.3",
    "debug": "~2.1.1",
    "express": "~4.11.1",
    "jade": "~1.9.1",
    "morgan": "~1.5.1",
    "serve-favicon": "~2.2.0",
    "socket.io": "^1.3.2"
-jQuery v2.1.3
-Bootstrap v3.3.2 (css and js)

---------------------------------------------------------------

Steps to execute:

a) Go to the project folder :
	cd ping-pong
b)Make sure all the node dependencies are installed.
	npm install
c)Start the node server
	node app.js
d) Open the url http://localhost:3000/ in the browser
e) All the server intiated ping message communications with the time stamp are shown on the right side column named as "Server Pings"
f) To send a ping from the client to the server click on button named "Click Here To Send Server Ping"
g) All the client intiated ping message communications with the time stamp are shown on the left side colum called as "Client Pings"
h) When a client receives a pong message from server it is displayed in the webconsole of the browser as well.
i) When a server recieves a pong message it displayed on the server logs
---------------------------------------------------------------
